<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,153,1043]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis box="[199,275,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Wings.</emphasis>
Forewing hyaline with most of the crossveins brown, amber areas surrounding M fork and posterior wing margin between CuP apex and first CuA branch (
<figureCitation box="[764,829,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1980,2005]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,185,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,185,1954]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, habitus of male holotype, lateral; b, wing venation." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235146/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); pterostigma brown with pale at middle, longitudinal veins alternate brown and pale; 10–12 costal crossveins posterior to humeral vein; three or four veins arising from 
<emphasis box="[151,215,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">rarp1</emphasis>
cell, two or three from 
<emphasis box="[481,544,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">rarp2</emphasis>
cell; five or six gradate veins on RP; hind wing hyaline with crossveins brown, wing margin dashed with brown and pale; six costal crossveins, pterostigma brown with a preapical area pale; three or four veins arising from 
<emphasis box="[446,509,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">rarp1</emphasis>
cell, one or two from 
<emphasis box="[759,823,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">rarp2</emphasis>
cell; four gradate crossveins on RP.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,153,1043]" box="[199,934,369,395]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis box="[199,313,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Mostly pale with brown areas; pleural membrane dark.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,153,1043]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis box="[199,374,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Tergite 9 dark brown, dorsally narrower than laterally; ectoproct trapezoidal in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[160,242,441,467]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1981,2006]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,200,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[201,1386,200,1938]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, head and prothorax, lateral; b, forelegs; c, male terminalia, lateral; d, same, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235148/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
), rounded on posteroventral margin, with numerous fine and long setae; ventrally with a thickened ovoid lobe, mostly sclerotized with an arched, concave inner zone (
<figureCitation box="[852,937,477,504]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1981,2006]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,200,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[201,1386,200,1938]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, head and prothorax, lateral; b, forelegs; c, male terminalia, lateral; d, same, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235148/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Fig. 2d</figureCitation>
); sternite 9 pentagonal in ventral view with posterolateral sides rounded (
<figureCitation box="[490,577,513,540]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1981,2006]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,200,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[201,1386,200,1938]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, head and prothorax, lateral; b, forelegs; c, male terminalia, lateral; d, same, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235148/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Fig. 2d</figureCitation>
), trapezoidal in lateral view with a pointed posteroventral process, setose, posteroventrally swollen; mediuncus elongate, slightly expanded basally (
<figureCitation box="[1002,1087,549,575]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1872,1897]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,1070,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,1053,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, male genitalia, lateral; b, same, caudal; c, same, ventral.Abbreviations: g, gonarcus; gcx9, gonocoxite 9; hpm, hypomere; med, mediuncus; psp, pseudopenis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235150/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
), thickened, subparallel sided, with two median lateral short, blunt, and curved processes (
<figureCitation box="[821,905,585,612]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1872,1897]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,1070,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,1053,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, male genitalia, lateral; b, same, caudal; c, same, ventral.Abbreviations: g, gonarcus; gcx9, gonocoxite 9; hpm, hypomere; med, mediuncus; psp, pseudopenis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235150/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
); pseudopenis thickened at base, long, strongly coiled, forming two loops, apex protruding from the abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[848,928,621,647]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1872,1897]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,1070,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,1053,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, male genitalia, lateral; b, same, caudal; c, same, ventral.Abbreviations: g, gonarcus; gcx9, gonocoxite 9; hpm, hypomere; med, mediuncus; psp, pseudopenis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235150/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
); a pair of hypomeres elongated and thin (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1872,1897]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,1070,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,1053,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, male genitalia, lateral; b, same, caudal; c, same, ventral.Abbreviations: g, gonarcus; gcx9, gonocoxite 9; hpm, hypomere; med, mediuncus; psp, pseudopenis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235150/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Fig. 3c</figureCitation>
); the base of pseudopennis and distal half of mediuncus protected by a dorsal semimembranous dome (
<figureCitation box="[1347,1422,657,683]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1872,1897]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,1070,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,1053,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, male genitalia, lateral; b, same, caudal; c, same, ventral.Abbreviations: g, gonarcus; gcx9, gonocoxite 9; hpm, hypomere; med, mediuncus; psp, pseudopenis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235150/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Fig 3a</figureCitation>
), ventrally connected to hypomeres; gonarcus median lobe with two differentiated parts: dorsal one with apical region bent dorsad (
<figureCitation box="[294,375,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1872,1897]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,1070,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,1053,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, male genitalia, lateral; b, same, caudal; c, same, ventral.Abbreviations: g, gonarcus; gcx9, gonocoxite 9; hpm, hypomere; med, mediuncus; psp, pseudopenis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235150/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
), narrower medially and expanded laterally, forming a rounded lobe in caudal view; ventral part with a short bulging, and a short ventral curved projection, between these parts a semicircular window is present (
<figureCitation box="[160,245,801,828]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1872,1897]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,1070,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,1053,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, male genitalia, lateral; b, same, caudal; c, same, ventral.Abbreviations: g, gonarcus; gcx9, gonocoxite 9; hpm, hypomere; med, mediuncus; psp, pseudopenis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235150/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
); gonarcus arms elongated, straight, basally slightly curved (
<figureCitation box="[940,1023,801,827]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1872,1897]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,1070,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,1053,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, male genitalia, lateral; b, same, caudal; c, same, ventral.Abbreviations: g, gonarcus; gcx9, gonocoxite 9; hpm, hypomere; med, mediuncus; psp, pseudopenis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235150/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
); gonocoxite 9 elongated, thickened with distal half curved laterodorsally (
<figureCitation box="[581,663,837,863]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1872,1897]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,1070,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,1053,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, male genitalia, lateral; b, same, caudal; c, same, ventral.Abbreviations: g, gonarcus; gcx9, gonocoxite 9; hpm, hypomere; med, mediuncus; psp, pseudopenis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235150/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
), slightly expanded basally and curved dorsally, apically with 10–13 spines of different size, subparallel, pectinately arranged (
<figureCitation box="[799,877,873,899]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1872,1897]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,1070,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,1053,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, male genitalia, lateral; b, same, caudal; c, same, ventral.Abbreviations: g, gonarcus; gcx9, gonocoxite 9; hpm, hypomere; med, mediuncus; psp, pseudopenis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235150/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[890,933,873,899]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1983,2008]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,548,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,536,1949]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 13. Plega spp., male gonocoxites 9: a, P. mixteca sp. n.; b, P. sonorae sp. n.; c, P. spinosa sp. n.; d, P. stangei sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235166/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">13a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
