<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="356" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,153,1043]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,981,1007]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named after the prehispanic mixtecan culture, that lived in part of the Pacific coast and central 
<collectingCountry box="[282,370,1017,1043]" name="Mexico" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, in the current states of 
<collectingRegion box="[637,741,1017,1043]" country="Mexico" name="Guerrero" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Guerrero</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[752,839,1017,1043]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[898,978,1017,1043]" country="Mexico" name="Puebla" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Puebla</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
